# Basics

1. Running individual tests in PyTest using PyCharm options...
     --> File > Settings > Tools > Python Integrated Tools > Default Test Runner...
     --> Change Default Test Runner > PyTest (Option)

2. Generating Allure Report...
     --> Install Java
     --> Install Node.js
     --> Install Allure Command Line Tool
            --> Command in CMD --> npm install -g allure-commandline
     --> Go and copy --> C:\Users\<ID>\AppData\Roaming\npm\node_modules\allure-commandline\bin
     --> Open PowerShell as Administrator
     --> Type Allure and Confirm
     --> Type Get-ExecutionPolicy in PowerShell (The output should be RemoteSigned)
     --> If not, use --> Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned --> And confirm it...
     --> Type Allure and Confirm again in Command Prompt/PowerShell
     --> Install Allure --> pip install allure-pytest
     --> Execute this command in PyCharm Terminal --> pytest --alluredir="./reports"
            --> The above command will execute the scripts...
     --> Open the project location and open the cmd with location and execute below command in cmd...
            --> allure serve "./Reports"

